  Bug #206800 - Fix epydoc command to work with epydoc-3.0.

*portage-2.1.4 (11 Jan 2008)

  12 Jan 2008; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4.ebuild:
  2.1.4 final release. This fixes bugs #203316, #203887, #204425,
  #204651, #204668, #204753, and #205318. Bug #200044 tracks all bugs
  fixed since 2.1.3.x.

*portage-2.1.4_rc14 (31 Dec 2007)

  31 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.4_rc13.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.4_rc14.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc14 fixes bug #203918 (NameError when using PORTAGE_BINHOST).

*portage-2.1.4_rc13 (31 Dec 2007)

  31 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.4_rc12.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.4_rc13.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc13 fixes a regression from 2.1.4_rc12 that triggered incorrect
  USE=test calculation in some cases when FEATURES=test was enabled.

*portage-2.1.4_rc12 (30 Dec 2007)

  30 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc12.ebuild:
  The 2.1.4_rc12 release fixes bugs #121584, #201498, #202697,
  #203090, #203239, #203323, and #203625. Bug #200044 tracks all
  bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

*portage-2.1.4_rc11 (21 Dec 2007)

  21 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc11.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc11 bump. This fixes bugs #149816 (support for binary package
  masking and other visibility filtering), and #176467 (limit values in
  $USE to ones in $IUSE). Bug #200044 tracks all bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

