*portage-2.1.4_rc9 (08 Dec 2007)

  08 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc9.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc9 fixes environment leakage from make.conf so that an ebuild
  can unset a variable like LDFLAGS and rely on it remaining unset for
  the following phases (bug #189417).

*portage-2.1.4_rc8 (07 Dec 2007)

  07 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.4_rc7.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.4_rc8.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc8 regression fix for bug #201506 (sandbox violation with packages
  that inherit from qt3.eclass).

*portage-2.1.4_rc7 (04 Dec 2007)

  04 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.4_rc6.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.4_rc7.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc7 regression fix for bugs #201082 (CATEGORY unset during postinst)
  and #201090 (issues reinstalling portage when /tmp is mounted noexec).
  Bug #200044 tracks all bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

*portage-2.1.4_rc6 (03 Dec 2007)

  03 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.4_rc5.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.4_rc6.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc6 regression fix. This solves an issue with sandbox violations
  triggered by having the CCACHE_DIR variable exported in the calling
  environment.

*portage-2.1.4_rc5 (03 Dec 2007)

  03 Dec 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc5.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc5 bump. This fixes bugs #189417, #200652, #200775, and #200863.
  Bug #200044 tracks all bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

*portage-2.1.4_rc4 (28 Nov 2007)

  28 Nov 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc4.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc4 bump. This fixes bugs #200229, #200231, #200238, and #200313.
  The most important fix is Bug #200229 which triggers gimp build failures
  due to AA being readonly. Bug #200044 tracks all bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

  24 Nov 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc3.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc3 bump. This version adds support for persistence of colon
  separated SANDBOX_{DENY,READ,PREDICT,WRITE} variables between phases
  so things like the global scope addpredict() call in qt3.eclass will
  continue to work.

*portage-2.1.4_rc2 (23 Nov 2007)

  23 Nov 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc2.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc2 bump. This version makes the bashrc behavior in the ebuild
  environment more compatible with older versions of portage. Now the
  full environment will be available to the bashrc like it used to be,
  which solves an issue with grep hanging indefinitely in
  default-bsd/profile.bashrc.

*portage-2.1.4_rc1 (23 Nov 2007)

  23 Nov 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.4_rc1.ebuild:
  2.1.4_rc1. This fixes bugs #46223, #190128, #198398, #198491, #198492,
  and #199311. This release includes new environment processing support
  which solves bugs #46223 and #190128. Now an ebuild and it's eclasses
  are only sourced once, and the resulting bash environment is reused for
  the entire lifecycle of the package. This allows eclasses to have
  incompatible api changes or be completely removed from the tree without
  causing problems for installed packages. It also allows environment
  variables to persist through the entire lifecycle of a package. For
  example, a binary package has access to the build time environment, and
  a package being uninstalled has access to the build time and install
  time environments. Bug #200044 tracks all bugs fixed since 2.1.3.x.

